tty_images/969910150/image_969910150.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/969910150/image_969910150.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/969910150/image_969910150.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">pookpiik/iStock via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <h2>Market Overview</h2> <p>US equities rose for the fourth consecutive quarter, with gains broadening beyond mega-cap tech companies. The equal-weighted S&amp;P 500 Index outperformed the market-cap weighted version, and value stocks outpaced growth stocks. The US economy remained healthy, with Q2</p>", "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/969910150/image_969910150.jpg", "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/article/4745295-hartford-midcap-value-fund-q3-2024-commentary", "pub_date": "2024-12-19 15:55:00"}, {"id": "4745294", "title": "First Bancorp: Earnings To Grow But Stock Appears Overvalued", "description": "<figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392870397/image_1392870397.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"First Bank building, Mooresville, NC\" data-id=\"1392870397\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"1024px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392870397/image_1392870397.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392870397/image_1392870397.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/1392870397/image_1392870397.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/up